title: Undead (attribute)

properties.name: description
properties.value: The undead attribute provides weaknesses to the salve amulet and the Crumble Undead spell.

content:
This article is about the undead monster type. For the race, see Undead.

The undead attribute provides weaknesses to the salve amulet and the Crumble Undead spell.

Contents

  • 1 Effects
  • 2 List of monsters
  • 3 Excluded monsters
  • 4 References

Effects[edit | edit source]

  • The salve amulet will provide the player with a 16.67% boost to Attack and Strength. The imbued version will additionally provide a 16.67% boost to Ranged and a 15% boost to Magic. This does not stack with the Slayer helmet.
  • The salve amulet (e) will provide the player with a 20% boost to Attack and Strength. The imbued version will additionally provide a 20% boost to Ranged and Magic. This does not stack with the Slayer helmet.
  • The Crumble Undead spell may only be used against monsters with the undead attribute. Requiring level 39 Magic, it has a max hit of 15 and only costs 1 chaos rune and some elemental runes.

Excluded monsters[edit | edit source]

Despite appearing to be ghosts, the Barrows brothers do not have the undead attribute. Additionally, monsters in the Nightmare Zone are not considered undead.[1]
